[
    {
        "content": "<p>I have a hypothesis about an integer <code>a</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span>\n<span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'd like to turn this into </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span>\n<span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>based on the idea that the successor to 2 is 3. </p>\n<p>How can I do this?</p>\n<p>(I've searched Moogle with no success, using search terms including gte of gt, succ, integer)</p>",
        "id": 469234426,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726012093
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does <code>replace hb : a ≥ 3 := by omega</code> work?</p>",
        "id": 469239291,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1726014104
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The best way to solve issues like this is to ask Lean about it:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">apply?</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>or rw? instead of apply? if it's about a rewrite</p>\n<p>In this case, \"exact hb\" is the answer, since a &lt; b is defined as (a + 1) &lt;= b and thus b &gt; a is defined as b &gt;= (a + 1)</p>",
        "id": 469240081,
        "sender_full_name": "lyphyser",
        "timestamp": 1726014500
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for the replies. </p>\n<p>I'm a beginner and at this point in the course (Heather Macbeth's) we aren't expected to use advanced tactics like <code>omega</code> or asking lean via <code>?</code></p>\n<p>I think we are expected to search for simpler lemmas like <code>le_or_gt</code>.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>The exercise is simple to express: </p>\n<p><code>example {m : ℤ} (h : ∃ a, 2 * a = m) : m ≠ 5 := by</code></p>\n<p>And the hint is to use a proof by cases, which suggests splitting <code>a</code> into something like <code>a &lt;= 2</code> and <code>a &gt;2</code>. The first case I can do, the second seems to require me to transition from <code>a&gt;2</code> to <code>a&gt;=3</code> by virtue of <code>a</code> being an integer.</p>",
        "id": 469363464,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726052386
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm currently searching moogle for \"​gt equals gte successor\" and <code>Order.lt_succ_iff_eq_or_lt</code> looks related but the wrong way around, there doesn't appear to be a <code>gt</code> version.</p>",
        "id": 469368482,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726053641
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You should treat <code>x &gt; y</code> as an illusion and imagine that it is <code>y &lt; x</code>: Lean will play along.</p>",
        "id": 469368909,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1726053773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe there's <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.add_one_le_of_lt#doc\">docs#Nat.add_one_le_of_lt</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 469369230,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1726053868
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fyi to talk about successors of natural numbers, just use <code>a + 1</code></p>",
