        "id": 469392955,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726060145
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Derek - thanks for the info on Mechanics of Proof.</p>\n<p>Launching the code in the online web \"live.lean\" environment also shows the unknown tactic error.</p>",
        "id": 469393752,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726060357
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>@rzeta0, I just tried out your code on my machine, and found that using <code>apply</code> worked:</p>\n<p><code>have hb2 : a ≥ 3 := by apply Int.add_one_le_of_lt hb</code></p>",
        "id": 469395017,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726060690
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>add_one_le_of_lt</code> is a theorem, which, if is an equality or an iff, then they can also be <code>rw</code> rewritten, but not used as a tactic, that is by itself in tactic mode.</p>\n<p>another way to do it is with term mode like:<br>\n<code>have hb2 : a ≥ 3 := Int.add_one_le_of_lt hb</code></p>",
        "id": 469395989,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726060929
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks Derek - the use of <code>apply</code> worked. I am a beginner so still learning the syntax but I think I do understand the different between applying a lemma and justifying via a tactic .. i think.</p>\n<p>Can I ask why the code doesn't work if I leave out the <code>Int</code> at the beggining of <code>Int.add_one_le_of_lt</code> ?</p>",
        "id": 469399066,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726061652
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Overall I think Macbeth has a simpler solution in mind as my resulting code seems far too big for this early chapter in her course. Am I missing a mathematical idea?</p>",
        "id": 469399210,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726061702
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>import Std.Data.Int.Basic</code> (edited) will bring the identifiers contained in the <code>Int</code> package into scope.  For some reason <code>Int</code> itself is in scope, not sure why.</p>\n<p>As for <code>apply</code>, at first it seemed backwards to me because I was used to <code>apply</code> from lisp.  Here are two contrived examples, the first is how <code>apply</code> seems to consume the last term of a chain of applications.  The second example shows how hypothesis can be applied like functions the way programmers are used to seeing it:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hc</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">-- goal ⊢ a &lt; c</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"c1\">-- (works backwards through the implication)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">-- goal ⊢ a &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">addarith</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hc</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">addarith</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">-- (how programmers usually think about function application)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- &lt;====</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">--</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 469449004,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726070553
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oops, I should have said that it is necessary to <code>open Int</code> before using <code>add_one_le_of_lt hb</code> without the <code>Int.</code> prefix</p>\n<p>and that the import should be <code>import Std.Data.Int.Basic</code> instead.</p>",
        "id": 469471276,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726075850
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"317929\">@Derek Rhodes</span> \"Apply\" is as in \"by applying theorem foo, we see it suffices to show...\" in a written proof.</p>\n<p><code>apply h</code> is more-or-less the same as <code>refine h ?_ ?_ ... ?_</code> with the correct number of <code>?_</code>s. It's applying the theorem in the function application sense too, just with as-yet-unknown arguments.</p>",
        "id": 469473903,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1726076716
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for the insight Kyle, now I have a reason to take a deeper look into <code>refine</code>.</p>",
        "id": 469474593,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726076918
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>refine</code> is <code>exact</code> except it allows placeholders that create new goals.</p>",
        "id": 469474752,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1726076963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok cool, good to know</p>",
        "id": 469474841,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1726076987
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm pretty sure that <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"260507\">@Heather Macbeth</span> prefers to use more tactic-based proofs, so probably the proof here is <code>linarith</code> or <code>addarith</code> or similar, rather than referring explicitly to the lemma <code>Int.add_one_le_of_lt</code> by name</p>",
        "id": 469631895,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1726137728
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110049\">Mario Carneiro</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/changing.20gt.20to.20gte.20for.20integers/near/469631895\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm pretty sure that <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> prefers to use more tactic-based proofs, so probably the proof here is <code>linarith</code> or <code>addarith</code> or similar, rather than referring explicitly to the lemma <code>Int.add_one_le_of_lt</code> by name</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I'd welcome ideas here. I spent quite a few hours trying to find a maths proof that was translatable into the small set of tactics we've covered but I couldn't see it.</p>",
        "id": 469692393,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726151444
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <a href=\"https://hrmacbeth.github.io/math2001/02_Proofs_with_Structure.html#sq-ne-two\">Example 2.3.2</a> has the lemma you want: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_or_succ_le</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>produces</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 469695122,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1726152066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks Heather Macbeth - I'll  give that a go.</p>\n<p>I'm working my way through the course doing every single exercise - doing the last two from the Existence chapter now.</p>\n<p>Thank you for creating this course. <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span></p>",
        "id": 469697121,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726152472
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yep - that works beautifully: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- have h3 := le_or_gt a 2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_or_succ_le</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">numbers</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ne_of_lt</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">numbers</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ne_of_gt</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g2</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 469697646,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1726152593
    }
]